Deposit money banks in the country would have to increase their cash reserves with the Central Bank of Nigeria as the monetary policy committee of the bank voted to raise cash reserve ratio to 27.5%. With a vote of nine out of 11 members, the committee agreed that the monetary policy rate, which impacts interest rate, should remain at 13.5%. Godwin Emefiele, the CBN governor, announced this on Friday after a two-day meeting of the committee. More details laterâ€¦ TheCable